      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOMBOK (10) made a nice return at her latest appearance two weeks ago, racing wide early before settling outside the leader and sticking on well to finish 2.6 metres away in second at this circuit and distance. Has won second-up before so should be improved. Strong claims if things go her way from the back row. MAJOR HAYLEY (3) has been competitive with a string of top-four finishes of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 7.5 metres from the winner after drawing wider and working. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw so she is a winning hope. AVA LEANNE (2) is race fit now and is on the radar after her last-start fourth from the same barrier here a week ago. LESSISMORE (4) drew wide and was held up in finishing fourth here last time out. Recorded back-to-back seconds prior. Contender from a better draw.",
